fields.description:
Configuring a ClearCase with a view location that has a trailing {{/}} will cause an error to be thrown in the logs and will stop indexing of the repository.

Example configuration:

{noformat}<clearcase viewLocation="/view/testing/" indexStartDate="2009-01-01" viewStorageLocation="" ucm="false" integrationOnly="false" includeIntegrationActivities="false" autoCreateView="false">{noformat}

Results in the following error:

{noformat}
15:45:20 ERROR - Invalid version id : com/atlassian/Test.java@@/main/Test.Java/1
15:45:20 WARN - Error executing command (desc -fmt %On "com/atlassian/Test.java@@/main/Test.Java/0" ) :
{noformat}

From https://support.atlassian.com/browse/FSH-3606

When FishEye attempts to process ClearCase symlinks, a 'Invalid Version Id' error appears in the logs.

Another support request with a similar problem: https://support.atlassian.com/browse/FSH-4803

When a symbolic link is deleted, FishEye assumes the output of the diff for the directory containing the symlink is a path, but cleartool uses a different syntax for symbolic links:

{noformat}
doctn -> ..\vob1\doctn 13-Aug.	08:44 akp
{noformat}

instead of 

{noformat}
obj2 12-Aug.14:00 akp
{noformat}

for regular files

FishEyes ClearCase support uses an interactive ClearCase client for a number of operations. This is basically a long-running {{cleartool}} shell that is kept around to limit the overhead of executing cleartool commands. However, our CleartoolInteractiveProcess ignores the error stream completely (it is not read), which causes FishEye to miss any error messages describing error conditions.

In some cases, Cleartool returns a status 0 (no error) but writes an error to the errorstream. One such example is when you run 
{noformat}
lsactivity -fmt "%[versions]Cp" activity:adding_a_test_file@/fe_pvob
{noformat}

while you're not in a view directory. In this case {{cleartool -status}} will output the following

{noformat}
[atlassian@clearcase views]$ ct -status
cleartool 1> lsactivity -fmt "%[versions]Cp" activity:adding_a_test_file@/fe_pvob
cleartool: Error: No view context available
Command 1 returned status 0
cleartool 2> 
{noformat}

Text files are seen as binary and so can't be annotated or viewed in source properly

 !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 

After further investigation, there are a couple of stray binary characters

{code}
0000000 357 273 277   /   *       L   o   c   a   l   i   z   e   d    
0000020   v   e   r   s   i   o   n   s       o   f       I   n   f   o
0000040   .   p   l   i   s   t       k   e   y   s       *   /  \n
{code}

However, this protection doesn't seem to work quite right?

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

{code}
0000000 357 273 277  ....
{code}
